\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {16}{\ignorespaces Comparison of EKF-estimated velocity against MoCap-derived velocity for representative Fixed Cage (left) and Rotating Cage (right) flights. The close agreement between the two traces through the impact and recovery phases validates that the onboard filter maintains estimation fidelity regardless of cage type, and that the rotating cage's reduced IMU excitation does not adversely affect state convergence.\relax }}{36}{figure.caption.31}\protected@file@percent }
