\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {18}{\ignorespaces Parallel coordinates visualisation of the top IMU features against impact angle for Rotating Cage (top) and Fixed Cage (bottom). Features are ordered left-to-right by descending |Pearson\nobreakspace  {}$r$| (computed on Rotating Cage data). Each polyline represents one flight, coloured by angle bin. The heavily overlapping trajectories across angle bins demonstrate exactly why simple linear thresholds fail: no single axis cleanly separates impact angles, motivating the Random Forest approach that follows.\relax }}{40}{figure.caption.34}\protected@file@percent }
